            <fr:title text="Baez-ian Special Linear Algebra for n\geq 3">Baez-ian Special Linear Algebra for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\geq 3]]></fr:tex></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Section 4 of <fr:link href="/petyt-2018-special/" title="The special linear group for nonassociative rings" uri="http://localhost:8000/petyt-2018-special/" display-uri="petyt-2018-special" type="local">[petyt-2018-special]</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a commutative unital associative <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">ring</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a finite-dimensional algebra over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> that is free as an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>-module (and have a basis <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{1}]]></fr:tex>, …, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{m}]]></fr:tex>).</html:p>
            <html:p>Write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {M}_{A}]]></fr:tex> for the left multiplication algebra of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>; i.e., <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {M}_{A}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>-algebra generated by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{L_{re_{i}}\mid  r\in  R\}]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is free over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {M}_{A}\subseteq \mathrm {End}_{R}(R^{m})=M_{m}(R).]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>Under these assumptions, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\geq 3]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {sl}_{n}(A)\cong \{x\in \mathrm {Mat}_{n}(\mathfrak {M}_{A})\mid \mathrm {tr}(x)\in [\mathfrak {M}_{A},\mathfrak {M}_{A}]\}.]]></fr:tex>
In particular, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {sl}_{n}(A)\subseteq \mathfrak {sl}_{mn}(R)]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
