            <fr:title text="Baez-ian Special Linear Group over Octonions">Baez-ian Special Linear Group over Octonions</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>corollary</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Corollary 4.2 in <fr:link href="/petyt-2018-special/" title="The special linear group for nonassociative rings" uri="http://localhost:8000/petyt-2018-special/" display-uri="petyt-2018-special" type="local">[petyt-2018-special]</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>In particular, for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\geq 3]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {SL}_{n}(\mathbb {O})\cong \mathrm {SL}_{8n}(\mathbb {R})]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>From the <fr:link href="/sl-0007/" title="Baez-ian Special Linear Algebra for n\geq 3" uri="http://localhost:8000/sl-0007/" display-uri="sl-0007" type="local">previous theorem</fr:link>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {sl}_{n}(\mathbb {O})\cong \mathfrak {sl}_{8n}(\mathbb {R})]]></fr:tex>. Then exponentiating this gives the result.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
<html:p>Compare this to Sudbery's definition, Eq (5.5) in <fr:link href="/sudbery-1984-division/" title="Division algebras, (pseudo)orthogonal groups and spinors" uri="http://localhost:8000/sudbery-1984-division/" display-uri="sudbery-1984-division" type="local">[sudbery-1984-division]</fr:link>, for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {sl}_{n}(\mathbb {O})]]></fr:tex> as left multiplication by traceless elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {h}_{n}(\mathbb {O})]]></fr:tex> together with its derivations. Chevalley and Schafer's "<fr:link href="/chevalley-1950-exceptional/" title="The Exceptional Simple Lie Algebras F4 and E6" uri="http://localhost:8000/chevalley-1950-exceptional/" display-uri="chevalley-1950-exceptional" type="local">The Exceptional Simple Lie Algebras F4 and E6</fr:link>" prove this is isomorphic with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {e}_{6}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p></fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
