            <fr:title text="Baez-ian Special linear group over the octonions">Baez-ian Special linear group over the octonions</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Section 2 and Theorem 4.1 in <fr:link href="/petyt-2018-special/" title="The special linear group for nonassociative rings" uri="http://localhost:8000/petyt-2018-special/" display-uri="petyt-2018-special" type="local">[petyt-2018-special]</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>There are several different ways to construct a group over the Octonions analogous to the special linear group.</html:p>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a (possibly nonassociative) <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">ring</fr:link> (possibly nonunital). If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_{i,j}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix which is 1 at row <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> and column <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex>, but zero everywhere else, then we define the group <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {SL}_{n}(R) = \langle  L_{I+aE_{i,j}}\mid  a\in  R, 1\leq  i\neq  j\leq  n\rangle ]]></fr:tex> to be generated by multiplying on the left by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I+aE_{i,j}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>For alternative algebras, this means
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[L_{E_{i}}L_{E_{i}}=L_{E_{i}^{2}}=\pm 1]]></fr:tex>
and for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_{i}\neq  E_{j}]]></fr:tex>, using the associator <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[z,w,u]=(zw)u-z(wu)]]></fr:tex> we have:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[0=[E_{i},E_{j},z] + [E_{j},E_{i},z] = L_{E_{i}E_{j}+E_{j}E_{i}}(z)-(L_{E_{i}}L_{E_{j}}+L_{E_{j}}L_{E_{i}})(z),]]></fr:tex>
and hence:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[L_{E_{i}}L_{E_{j}}=-L_{E_{j}}L_{E_{i}}.]]></fr:tex>
Using this, we have a precise, unambiguous ordering to the product of elements of the group.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
